% ============================================================
%  Axis Research Library — Master BibTeX Bibliography
%  axis-library.bib
% ============================================================
%
%  CITE-KEY CONVENTION
%  -------------------
%  Format:  authorYYYYkeyword
%  Rules:
%    author   = first author's surname, lowercase, ASCII-only,
%               hyphens and spaces removed
%               (e.g. Wikström-Frisén → wikstromfrisen)
%    YYYY     = four-digit publication year
%    keyword  = one lowercase word from the title that
%               distinguishes this entry from others by the
%               same author in the same year
%               (e.g. "resistance", "recovery", "phase")
%  Examples:
%    wikstromfrisen2017resistance
%    sung2014follicular
%    kissow2022performance
%
%  INTEGRITY RULES (see research/CITATION_STANDARDS.md)
%  -------------------
%  1. Every entry with a DOI must have a verified, live DOI.
%  2. Never invent a DOI. Use doi = {TODO:unverified} for
%     entries whose DOI has not yet been confirmed.
%  3. Unresolved entries must be marked with a note field:
%     note = {TODO: DOI unresolved — verify before publishing}
%  4. Run scripts/verify_refs.py before committing new entries.
%
%  CURRENT STATUS
%  -------------------
%  This file is scaffolded and empty. Add verified entries only.
%  Do NOT populate with unverified or invented references.
%
% ============================================================
